run().details: Deployer setup based on `ETH_KEYSTORE_ACCOUNT` in `.env`:      - "scaffold-eth-default": Uses Anvil's account #9 (0xa0Ee7A142d267C1f36714E4a8F75612F20a79720), no password prompt      - "scaffold-eth-custom": requires password used while creating keystore Note: Must use ScaffoldEthDeployerRunner modifier to:      - Setup correct `deployer` account and fund it      - Export contract addresses & ABIs to nextjs & scripts packages

documentation.text:
@dev Deployer setup based on `ETH_KEYSTORE_ACCOUNT` in `.env`:
      - "scaffold-eth-default": Uses Anvil's account #9 (0xa0Ee7A142d267C1f36714E4a8F75612F20a79720), no password prompt
      - "scaffold-eth-custom": requires password used while creating keystore
 Note: Must use ScaffoldEthDeployerRunner modifier to:
      - Setup correct `deployer` account and fund it
      - Export contract addresses & ABIs to nextjs & scripts packages

@notice Deploy script for Challenge2Solution contract
 @dev Inherits ScaffoldETHDeploy which:
      - Includes forge-std/Script.sol for deployment
      - Includes ScaffoldEthDeployerRunner modifier
      - Provides `deployer` variable
 Example:
 yarn deploy --file DeploySolution2.s.sol  # local anvil chain
 yarn deploy --file DeploySolution2.s.sol --network optimism # live network (requires keystore)
